# SYF Documentation — Canonical Structure

**Version:** 1.0  
**Status:** SEALED

---

## Overview

This repository contains the canonical documentation for the **Systemic Fire Law (SYF)**, 
**Anathema**, and related security architecture.

---

## Document Hierarchy

```
SYF-DOCS/
│
├── core/                           # FOUNDATIONAL (Read First)
│   ├── SYF_FOUNDATION.md          # Why SYF exists
│   ├── R_INVARIANT.md             # The systemic invariant R
│   └── SYF_ANATHEMA_BRIDGE.md     # How SYF becomes Anathema
│
├── security/                       # SECURITY MODEL
│   ├── SECURITY_MODEL.md          # Threat model & guarantees
│   ├── COMPARISON_CLASSIC.md      # SYF vs traditional security
│   ├── WHY_DETECTION_FAILS.md     # Why SYF doesn't detect
│   └── BREAKER_QA.md              # Anathema Breaker Q&A
│
├── implementation/                 # HOW TO USE
│   ├── R_SPEC_TEMPLATE.md         # Required spec for R projection
│   ├── R_FAQ.md                   # Developer questions
│   └── R_FAILURE_MODES.md         # What happens when things break
│
└── education/                      # HUMAN EXPLANATIONS
    └── ANATHEMA_SOFT_EXPLAINED.md # CTO/Engineer cheatsheet
```

